===subject:La Mordida - que horible!
===from:Arlo Hanlin Hemphill
===email:ahemphil@nova.edu
===institution_site:http://www.nova.edu/ocean
===institution:NSUOC
===date:Tue Jan 28 22:53:55 2003
===message:Hey Michele,

This is just an awful story, I am just horrified.  However, I agree with Dr. Schmidt, it is rampant in the developing world and not just in areas of conservation.  In most places that I have visited, you can pay your way out of any situation or into any situation as the case may be.  Unfortunately, this includes the need to often pay police to make arrests or even buy them gas for their car and bullets for their guns if you need their assistance.  In Ecuador, I have also noticed that a lot of times it is the park guards/rangers who are the biggest poachers.  When you have 5 kids to feed, you make a salary of $100/month, and you grew up in a farming community, it just seems like nonsense to let perfectly good game meet go to waste because the rich American tourists want to take pictures.
=========yorg=========
