===subject:complete agreement
===from:Michelle
===date:Sun Feb  2 18:34:42 2003
===message:Thanks, Arlo--
I totally agree with you. Which goes back to the money issue. If developed countries cannot control such issues, then it seems as if developing and underdeveloped countries are doomed. I wonder in what way we have to approach issues in such areas where surviving day-to-day is the driving force in people's lives. I feel like the reason so many people involved in international management get so frustrated is because they are trying to handle issues in the same ways they would in the U.S., or Europe, when the reality is, such different lifestyles require completely different approaches. If only I could figure out what these approaches could be... ;) 
=========yorg=========
